Connector Street is a smart phone app that allows users to introduce two contacts or friends instantly, safely and securely without a big investment of time, effort, or resources. Because both contacts/friends know and trust the introducer, the introduction is valued and effective. HOW IT WORKSOnce the user downloads the app and completes her profile, the app is ready to go. The user selects two contacts/friends from the contacts in her phone. (The user can also type her contacts'/friends' names and cell numbers/emails directly into the app and save that contact information into her contacts.) The user chooses the introduction type: business, social, or romantic. The user sends both contacts/friends a quick message using the app's pre-loaded introductions or creates a customized message. Once the introducer hits the Send button, the introducer's two contacts/friends receive the same introductory message, plus each receives the other's contact information. The two can begin messaging immediately from the in-app messaging system or via email or text. The app enables the introducer to save customized messages and build a library of introductions. The app stores all introductions and connections.

job_description: Healing Adults & Adolescents Residential Treatment Program (HAART) provides community-based residential care for adults. Each home must be licensed by the Division of Health Care Quality Office of Long Term Care Residents Protection and by the Delaware Medical Assistance Program {DMAP). HAART is a home that promotes healing for adults 18 years and older with severe and persistent mental illnesses, who may also have a substance abuse history. The Program gives residents an optimal chance at recovery and becoming productive members of society, while being reintegrated into their communities. HAART believes in psychosocial rehabilitation. Residents are empowered to safely live in the community with all supports needed to assist them with increasing their ability to improve their life outcomes. We center our treatment on the whole person and focus on their educational goals, vocational goals, medical needs, social/emotional needs, psychiatric needs, enhancing everyday living skills and building resiliency. Family involvement is highly encouraged and very important in our goal to assist residents with their treatment goals and integration into the community. HAART will support residents and their families with resources to remain engaged in the design and implementation of the resident's person centered recovery plan. Homes are staffed 24 hours 7 days a week. Each shift has a bachelor's level clinician to provide scheduled and as needed individual therapy as well as group therapy. A nurse is available 8 hours a day for dispensing medication and assessing medicneeds. A psychiatrist is available one day per week for psychotropic medication management and to assess other medical needs and make appropriate referrals. A master's level clinician is available for 8 hours per day to design and direct the implementation of the behavior modification person centered treatment/recovery plans.

Here at JennyGems we aren't just in the home decor business - we want to help people celebrate their milestones, embrace their uniqueness, and connect with their loved ones on a deeper level. We use our passion of designing and making wooden signs to encourage everyone to put a personal touch in every gift; whether it be a birthday, mother's day, father's day, Christmas, or any important occasion. We also support the celebration of everyone's unique passions. Including sports, travel, pets and animals, people, humor, their careers and professions or alcohol. We understand life is all about relationships, and make it easy to tell your grandparents, sisters, parents, and best friends just how much they mean to you! With thousands of original designs, anyone is sure to find just the perfect sign for every occasion. We adore helping people use their individualistic taste to make their house a home! Most people feel drawn to wooden signs for their visual appeal. Which is understandable; they absolutely add undeniable charm to almost any residential or business setting. Our signs embrace our motto of Fun, Happy, Stuff! We offer a wide variety of welcome signs, farmhouse signs, kitchen signs, bathroom humor signs, and even nursery signs. We also have signs for businesses but just because you want your sign to serve a practical purpose doesn't mean it can't be aesthetically pleasing, too! All of our products are made from real quality wood using state of the art UV printers and wood shop equipment. To keep the importance of individualistic taste, we offer a variety of display options. We route slots for hanging, or add sawtooth hooks on the back, and even attach genuine hemp rope for a rustic feel. Many of our signs can sit freely on their own on a shelf, desk, tabletop, or mantel. Over the past year, JennyGems has made a significant transition from importing products from China to making our own products in our home state of Delaware. With the addition of many new employees, more than 50% of which are women, we strive to help empower other women to their highest potential. We have a vast array of tastes, opinions and creativity among our team to help us ensure there is something for everyone. Any new product idea can be graphically designed, and created all in the same day. We very carefully inspect every product for the highest possible quality. For every meaningful moment, JennyGems is there to help commemorate the occasion.

Keywords: training, coaching, consulting At LearningCoreleadership, we shift mindset. We help providers, teams, and healthcare organizations move from the default self-focus of an inward mindset to the results-focus of an outward mindset. Through training, coaching, consulting, and our deep connection with and understanding of your health and healthcare challenges, we enable your organizations and people to achieve results that are only possible with an outward mindset, when they see the problem they don't see and become alive to the breadth of opportunities and options for achieving their goals, needs, and objectives. We help individuals, teams and organizations tackle three major challenges: Creating Collaborative Cultures Many healthcare organizations operate in a hierarchical, top-down culture that can hinder collaboration and foster conflict. The cross-functional collaboration and communication that are key to ensuring consistent clinical outcomes are undermined by the real or perceived differences in power, status, or influence that are a vestige of historical ways of operating in healthcare. We help providers, administrators and staff see their challenges differently to unleash their ability to better collaborate with and influence others. Improving Safety and Clinical Outcomes Many mistakes happen because individuals lack awareness of the impact of their actions on others within a healthcare system. With the health of patients at stake, and with increased bureaucratic scrutiny and oversight, improving safety and clinical outcomes is critically important. Our work helps overcome the many challenges in implementing process improvement, quality and safety initiatives wrought by hyper-attention to being procedurally correct while missing the opportunity to work as a team better. Research shows that low-functioning teams make far more errors and have worse outcomes than teams that work well together. Minimizing Risk and Increasing Patient Satisfaction Reigniting employee purpose and equipping healthcare professionals with the tools to effectively collaborate and communicate is key to minimizing risk and improving patient access, flow, and satisfaction. The mindset of healthcare professionals toward patients-what researchers have termed bedside manner and patient centricity -is a critical factor in the perceptions of patients regarding the care they receive. We help healthcare professionals find the outward mindset connection to their patients and customers that invigorates the quality. confidence. and closeness of those relationships.
